.TH ZOPEN-ALT "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-alt \- manual page for zopen-alt 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-alt
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR] [\fI\,PARAMETERS\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-alt is a utility for zopen community to switch package versions
for currently installed packages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR, \-?
display this help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR [PACKAGE]
select the active version for PACKAGE from a list.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-set\fR [PACKAGE] [VERSION]
set the active version for PACKAGE to VERSION.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
run in verbose mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
print version
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
zopen alt foo
list the available alternatives for package 'foo'
.TP
zopen alt \-\-select foo
list the available alternatives for package 'foo'
and allow the user to select an alternative version
.TP
zopen alt \-\-set foo foo\-1.2.3.19700101_012345.zos
set the active version of package 'foo' to version
foo\-1.2.3.19700101_012345.zos if available
